1) Preheat to 400°F
2) Press tofu
3) Chop into cubes
4) Add 2 TBSP nutritional yeast, 1 TBSP soy sauce
5) Bake for ~20-30 mins, flipping halfway through

urls.description: 15 ounces extra firm tofu, drained 1 Tablespoon reduced sodium tamari or soy sauce 2 teaspoons unseasoned rice vinegar (no sodium, no sugar) 1teaspoon honey 3 Tablespoons nutritional yeast avocado or olive oil spray Preheat oven to 400 F. Line sheet pan with 2 layers of paper towels, or a clean cotton dish towel. Cut tofu into 1-inch wide planks, then cut those into 1-inch wide strips.
